# The living log — at-hand reference

Full protocol: `AGENTS.md` → *Read the knowledge first*.

Two knowledge files at the project root:

- `docs/brief.md` — original brief, immutable.
- `docs/knowledge.md` — living log; every decision, convention,
  gotcha, glossary term, dated `YYYY-MM-DD`.

## Authority order

```
training data  <  docs/brief.md  <  docs/knowledge.md  <  user in this chat
```

If the user contradicts the log in this chat, do the user's bidding
**and** update the log in the same PR.

## Every session

Read `docs/knowledge.md` before editing. Skim the Index, focus on
the sections touching your task.

## Every non-trivial PR

Update `docs/knowledge.md` in the same PR when the change
introduces any of: a new decision (even an agent-chosen default), a
new convention, a new gotcha that cost >10 min to debug, a new
domain term, or invalidates a prior entry (strike-through, don't
delete).

Cosmetic-only PRs (typo, format) are exempt. Short entries, dated,
grep-able. Link to PRs/files, don't paste.

## If the learning is generalizable

Prefix the entry with `GENERAL:` and stage an outbox entry — see
`gaia-sync.mdc`. The pre-push hook reminds you.
